H.B. 903
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
Apr 10, 2025
SESSION 2025
HOUSE PRINCIPAL CLERK
H D
HOUSE BILL DRH30276-NDfa-7A
Short Title: Highway and Road Safety Act. (Public)
Sponsors: Representative Logan.
Referred to:
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO INCREASE STATE TROOPERS IN MECKLENBURG COUNTY, TO
3 INCREASE MAGISTRATES IN MECKLENBURG COUNTY, TO REVISE CERTAIN
4 PENALTIES FOR FAILURE TO STOP FOR A SCHOOL BUS AND AUTHORIZE THE
5 USE OF VEHICLE REGISTRATION AS PRIMA FACIE EVIDENCE OF
6 RESPONSIBILITY, AND TO EXPAND THE OPERATIONAL HOURS OF THE NORTH
7 CAROLINA DEPARTMENT OF TRANSPORTATION METROLINA
8 TRANSPORTATION MANAGEMENT CENTER IN CHARLOTTE.
9 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
10
11 INCREASE TROOPERS IN MECKLENBURG COUNTY
12 SECTION 1.(a) There is appropriated from the General Fund to the State Highway
13 Patrol the sum of nine hundred ninety-nine thousand four hundred dollars ($999,400) in recurring
14 funds for the 2025-2026 fiscal year and one million eighty-eight thousand five hundred
15 ninety-two dollars ($1,088,592) in nonrecurring funds for the 2025-2026 fiscal year to be used
16 to fund 12 full-time State Trooper positions.
17 SECTION 1.(b) Notwithstanding G.S. 20-192 and any rules and regulations created
18 pursuant to that statute, the State Trooper positions funded in this act shall result in an increase
19 of at least 12 State Troopers assigned to State Highway Patrol District H5 of Troop H.
20 SECTION 1.(c) This section becomes effective July 1, 2025.
21
22 INCREASE MAGISTRATES IN MECKLENBURG COUNTY
23 SECTION 2.(a) G.S. 7A-133(c) reads as rewritten:
24 "(c) Each county shall have the numbers of magistrates and additional seats of district
25 court, as set forth in the following table:
26 Magistrates Additional
27 County Min. Seats of Court
28 …
29 Mecklenburg 38.543.5
30 …."
31 SECTION 2.(b) There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Administrative
32 Office of the Courts the sum of four hundred two thousand seventy dollars ($402,070) in
33 recurring funds for the 2025-2026 fiscal year and fifteen thousand one hundred forty dollars
34 ($15,140) in nonrecurring funds for the 2025-2026 fiscal year to be used to hire five additional
35 magistrates to serve in Mecklenburg County pursuant to subsection (a) of this section.
36 SECTION 2.(c) This section becomes effective July 1, 2025.
